{
  "name": "OneFlare Bot/Scraper Response - Graduated Cloudflare Mitigation (BotScore)",
  "description": "Fires on the S1 scheduled detection 'CF-Bot-Scraper (BotScore)' (rule 2523842940840264774), which flags a single src_ip producing >= 20 HTTP requests scored <= 29 by Cloudflare's ML BotScore against the soledrop.co lab surface. The workflow keys off Cloudflare's ML verdict (BotScore) - NOT the spoofable User-Agent. It extracts src_ip, re-derives the bot metrics in-flow from the detection's own source (class_uid 4002) via PowerQuery so it never depends on a spoofable field, enriches src_ip reputation via VirusTotal (ASN/AS-owner is the 'known bad hosting' signal), then decides: known-bad reputation OR high in-lab volume => hard BLOCK the IP at Cloudflare; otherwise => graduated managed_challenge (challenge-first is the correct bot response). Both paths add an evidence-backed S1 alert note, post to Slack, and email the SOC. run_automatically is false so an analyst approves the containment from the Singularity Response console. MITRE ATT&CK T1595 (Active Scanning), T1071 (Application Layer Protocol); MITRE ATLAS AML.T0002 (data reconnaissance via scraping).",
